  "description": "This morning dish leans on traditional South Indian technique but shifts the grain balance toward whole grains and lentils. Kuthiraivali Coconut Sevai brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat a wide pan on medium heat, add oil, mustard seeds, urad dal, and cook 45 seconds until the dal turns pale gold.",
    "Add curry leaves, ginger, chilli, onion, and vegetables; saute 3 to 4 minutes until just tender but still bright.",
    "Add the sevai, salt, and 40 ml water. Toss gently on low heat for 2 minutes so the strands absorb seasoning without breaking.",
    "Finish with grated coconut and toss once more. Rest 2 minutes before serving so the starch firms and the strands stay separate."
  ],
